      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i got a 2018 camry throwing a p0171 code (system too lean bank 1). already swapped the maf and it didnt change anything. what else should i be looking at for possible causes?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The P0171 code indicates that the engine is running lean on bank 1. Since replacing the Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor didn't solve the issue, consider checking the following: \n\n1. Faulty or dirty Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor on bank 2 or 3 (though less likely than bank 1 in some models).\n2. Vacuum leaks, especially before the throttle body (if applicable).\n3. A failing Mass Air Flow (MAF) heater.\n4. Faulty mass airflow sensor (MAF) fuse.\n\nTry these components first before moving on to more complex solutions.",
